        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 4:21PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles south of Kennedy Meadow, or 15 miles south of Sonora Pass,
moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paradise Meadow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
